originalText.text: Tacos and Tequila reminded us of our trip to Mexico City. The food was not your usual tacos and enchiladas but more authentic choices. And it was extremely well prepared, seasoned, flavorful, with just the right amount of spice. I had Camarones de Mexicana, large shrimp with peppers, onions, jalapeños. and my husband enjoyed Carne Asada smothered in onions.They have a lovely room in the back. The service was excellent. If you’re tired of the same old menu, try this restaurant. And have a custom drink while you’re there.

originalText.text: I would give zero if I could but that’s not an option.  First time eating at tacos and tequila- based on the reviews here I wasn’t expecting amazing food to begin with but I just wanted some tacos so I thought what can go wrong with just tacos. At the end of the day it’s a mexican restaurant !! Well .. things can go very wrong when the beef tacos I ordered were charted . I took a bite and asked my boyfriend what he thought. He agreed. I called the waiter and complained, he offered to replace the order.. so far nothing wrong . He takes my plate and the main plate, and returns few minutes later saying they would replace just one taco because the other two we had already started eating( sure had to take a bite ). I was shocked, and in absolute disbelief . He did replace the one taco ! Short story , if you go there expect bad food, and poor costumer service, not even an apology. For ordinary food there are 3 or 4 other Mexican restaurants in the same block.  Maybe you may not have amazing food but perhaps better costumer service.

originalText.text:
We really enjoyed our meal at Tacos & Tequila. We came here on a Saturday night as we wanted a local Mexican spot.

Ambiance: The restaurant looks a lot smaller than it actually is. There is a back section that is very cutely decorated and feels very in theme with a Mexican spot.

Drinks: They have a lot of drink options and they are definitely strong drinks. Our margaritas were very reasonably priced and considering they were strong and also delicious, we had no complaints. They also have "large" size drinks. We didn't try it this time but plan to the next time we go back. My husband also commented that he loves places that will give you a iced beer glass. He was very happy when he got his bottle of beer but then had an iced glass to pour it into.

Food: The menu is very extensive and there are a lot of different food options. As a vegetarian I was very impressed with the amount of veggie options that existed. They also had soyrizo, veggie tinga, and veggie pastor. I have yet to find all three at any Mexican spot in the city. I could not have been happier with all the options to pick from. The food was delicious and tasted fresh. We had the flautas, tostadas, and street tacos. All three entrees were well seasoned and tasted great. They also gave us salsas and one of them was so perfectly spicy, I was happy.

Service: The staff was very nice and considerate. Service was fast but we never felt rushed. The food did take a while to come out but after tasting it I understood it's because everything is fresh and made only after an order is placed.

originalText.text:
A nice cozy spot to have delicious food & drinks. The menu selection is great. They offer a variety of Mexican dishes that I love such as the chicken verde enchiladas, Chile relleno and tacos of course!

I was a bit surprised by the prices being a bit higher than what I am used to for a Mexican restaurants with similar cuisine. However, the portions and quality of food softened the blow of the check. You can’t deny they know how to cook. The drinks were strong and flavorful as  well. I would recommend this spot for a casual dining experience.
